1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:07,300
Your first program in Sanskrita — in just five minutes.
Let's begin!

2
00:00:07,700 --> 00:00:15,900
You need just two things — Python 3, already on most
computers, and our GitHub repo.

3
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:24,000
Open the Terminal. First clone the repo,
then type — bash install.sh.

4
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:28,500
That's it! Sanskrita is ready.

5
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:36,000
Now create a file — नमस्ते.सं.
And write in it — वद("नमस्ते जगत्")।

6
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:39,700
Don't forget the danda । at the end!

7
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:48,900
Now run it — sanskrita नमस्ते.सं.
And look — your first Sanskrit program just spoke!

8
00:00:49,300 --> 00:01:01,900
Devanagari typing feels hard? No problem.
Run sanskrita-playground — type in roman letters,
and it becomes Devanagari automatically!

9
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:15,800
What next? The repo has a full tutorial — ten programs
in an hour. Plus the AI-SPEC — turn any AI
into your personal Sanskrita guru!

10
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:24,300
So write your first program today — post it on GitHub
and tell us! Jayatu Sanskritam!
